Unit Number,Unit Title,Key Topics
Unit 1,Early American and Colonial Literature,"Puritan literature, Native American oral traditions, The Enlightenment in America"
Unit 2,The Romantic Period,"American Romanticism, Transcendentalism, Gothic Literature"
Unit 3,The American Renaissance and Realism,"Herman Melville, Walt Whitman, Emily Dickinson, Mark Twain, Henry James"
Unit 4,Naturalism and the Early 20th Century,"Theodore Dreiser, Jack London, Early Modernist Movements"
Unit 5,The Harlem Renaissance and Modernism,"Langston Hughes, Zora Neale Hurston, T.S. Eliot, F. Scott Fitzgerald, Ernest Hemingway"
Unit 6,Post-World War II Literature,"J.D. Salinger, Sylvia Plath, Postmodernism, Contemporary Voices"
Unit 7,Contemporary American Literature,"Toni Morrison, Don DeLillo, American Drama, Current Literary Trends"
Unit 8,American Poetry Across the Ages,"Poetic movements, Major American poets and their works"
Unit 9,The Short Story in America,"Evolution of the short story, Notable American short story writers"
Unit 10,The American Novel,"Development of the novel in America, Key novels and their impact on society"